<A HREF="FSOUND.html#Functions"><H5>[API function]</A></H5>
<H2><A NAME="FSOUND_Sample_Upload">FSOUND_Sample_Upload</A></H2>
This function uploads new sound data from memory to a preallocated/existing sample and does<BR>
conversion based on the specified source mode.<BR>
If sample data already exists at this handle then it is replaced with the new data being uploaded.<BR>
<P>
<B>signed char F_API </B><B> </B><B>FSOUND_Sample_Upload</B><B>(</B><BR>
<B>FSOUND_SAMPLE *</B><I>sptr</I><B>,</B><BR>
<B>void *</B><I>srcdata</I><B>,</B><BR>
<B>unsigned int </B><B> </B><I>mode</I><BR>
<B>);</B><BR>
<H3>Parameters</H3>
<TABLE>
<TR VALIGN=top><TD><I>sptr</I></TD>
<TD>Pointer to the destination sample<BR>
</TD><TR VALIGN=top><TD><I>srcdata</I></TD>
<TD>Pointer to the source data to be uploaded<BR>
</TD><TR VALIGN=top><TD><I>mode</I></TD>
<TD>Description of the source data format. Bitwise OR in these bits to describe the <BR>
data being passed.	See FSOUND_MODES for valid parameters and descriptions.<BR>
FSOUND_HW3D, FSOUND_HW2D and FSOUND_LOOP modes are ignored, the mode describes the <BR>
source format, not the destination format.<BR>
</TD></TABLE>
<H3>Return Value</H3>
On success, TRUE is returned.<BR>
On failure, FALSE is returned.<BR>
<H3>Remarks</H3>
___________________<BR>
Supported on the following platforms : Win32, WinCE, Linux, Macintosh, XBox, PlayStation 2, GameCube<BR>
